content: Welcome to Online Renju Class lesson
of course, today is a new year's eve, so we can soon see the year 2006 coming
This is the last lesson in year 2005.
Today, we will talk about one recent tournament, which ended just yesterday.
there was an international renju tournament in Estonia,
We have such international tournament every year.
This time, we had players from 4 countries.
The final standings after 8 rounds were:
I was first with 7 points, and Kozhin from Russia was 2nd with 6 points,
The interesting thing was that the tournament was not played by RIF rules,
but was used as a testing tournament,
black player has one extra option:
after which white cannot swap any more.
such additional option will avoid crazy far-away 4th moves.
for the black player it is difficult to decide what to do..
if he chooses to play next move,
and if black player chooses to swap now,
then maybe opponent has prepared a crazy 5th move too
its very hard to decide in short time
so the problem of standard "tarannikov" rule is,
it will let white play crazy 4th move
black can use the additional  option:
all of them are winning 5th moves
the white player cannot play crazy 4th moves
and this is good for renju
so, the whole tournament of Tallinn Open was used for testing this rule.
Today I will show you some games.
I will begin with most important game.
It was played in the last round between me and Kozhin,
we both had 6 points from 7 games at that moment.
and whoever was going to win that game, was to be the winner of the tournament as well
